rms  stability analysis  steady state and transient analysis  feedback control  continuous to discrete conversion  digital control  Course Information  Prerequisite s  Class Schedule Information   To be properly registered  students must enroll in one Laboratory and one Lecture Discussion  n   Computer Organization     hours  nSoftware hardware interaction in a computer  Compiler  assembler and linker  machine code  Clocking  datapath  control unit  ALU and memory design  cache memory  pipelining  Prerequisite s  n   Microprocessor Based Design     hours  nMicroprocessor architecture  microprogrammed machines  programmer s model  control signals and timing  system buses  parallel and serial interfacing  interrupt processing  I O devices  memory devices  direct memory access  assembly language  Laboratory  Course Information   Prerequisite s  Class Schedule Information   To be properly registered  students must enroll in one Laboratory Discussion and one Lecture Discussion  n   CAD Based Digital Design     hours  nSemi complex circuit and system design techniques  data path control using FSMs  VHDL programming  circuit system design projects using VHDL and CAD tools  VHDL Simulation  Circuit Synthesis  Laboratory  Prerequisite s  Class Schedule Information  To be properly registered  students must enroll in one Laboratory and one Lecture  n   Undergraduate Research       hours  nResearch under close supervision of a faculty member  Course Information  Satisfactory Unsatisfactory grading only  Prerequisite s   Consent of the instructor  n   Senior Design I     hours  nIntroduction to the principles and practice of product design  specifications  evaluation of design alternatives  technical reports  and oral presentations  Independent design projects  Course Information  Prerequisite s  Open only to seniors  n   Senior Design II     hours  nApplication of engineering principles and optimization to the solution of the design problem initiated in Electrical and Computer 